properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued February 8 at 3:09AM PST until February 10 at 4:00AM PST by NWS Reno NV
properties.description:
* CHANGES...Updates to wind direction for Lake Wind Advisory.

* WHAT...For the Lake Wind Advisory, west winds 10 to 20 mph with
gusts up to 40 mph expected shifting to northeast late this
evening and overnight. Waves 2 to 4 feet. For the Wind
Advisory, northeast winds 15 to 25 mph with gusts up to 50 mph
expected.

* WHERE...Greater Lake Tahoe Area.

* WHEN...For the Lake Wind Advisory, from 10 AM today to 10 AM
PST Sunday. For the Wind Advisory, from 10 AM Sunday to 4 AM PST
Monday.

* IMPACTS...Hazardous boating conditions for Lake Tahoe. Gusty
winds may blow around unsecured objects. Downed trees or tree
limbs could result in power outages.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Small boats, kayaks and paddle boards will
be prone to capsizing and should remain off lake waters until
conditions improve. Highest waves are expected on the eastern
shores today, but east winds on Sunday will shift the highest
waves on the western shores.
properties.instruction:
Now is the time to secure all loose outdoor items such as patio
furniture and trash cans before winds increase which could blow
these items away. The best thing to do is prepare ahead of time by
making sure you have extra food and water on hand, flashlights
with spare batteries and/or candles in the event of a power
outage.

NWSheadline: LAKE WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 10 AM THIS MORNING TO 10 AM PST SUNDAY FOR LAKE TAHOE... ...WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 10 AM SUNDAY TO 4 AM PST MONDAY
